  {
    "ts": "2026-03-24T11:45:30+00:00",
    "headline": "European car sales rise modestly in February, Tesla reverses skid",
    "summary": "<body><p>STORY: New car sales in Europe rose in February after falling in January.</p><p>And sustained demand for electric vehicles helped Tesla achieve growth for the first time since 2024.</p><p>Data from the European auto lobby the ACEA showed overall car registrations, a proxy for sales, in the EU, Britain and the European Free Trade Association were up 1.7%.</p><p>Over 979,000 cars were sold in the month, with two-thirds of those being electric or hybrid.&nbsp;</p><p>The EU and Britain are walking back some regulations aimed at reducing CO2 emissions.</p><p>That's after pressure from domestic carmakers who say they are struggling to turn a profit on EV sales...</p><p>while facing competition from Chinese rivals.</p><p>But battery-electric and plug-in hybrid sales have been steadily on the rise in Europe thanks to new, cheaper models.</p><p>The data showed Tesla's February registrations were up 11.8% year-on-year ...</p><p>They were marginally lower than those of its Chinese competitor BYD, whose sales more than doubled from the same month of 2025.</p><p>Sales of top domestic carmakers VW and Stellantis rose by 2.2% and 9.5%, respectively.</p><p>While Renault's fell by 14.3%.</p></body>",
    "url": "https://finance.yahoo.com/video/european-car-sales-rise-modestly-114530597.html",
    "source": "Reuters Videos",
